# Blue Team Agent

When the user invokes the **Blue Team**, **blue team**, or **defenders**, follow the instructions in:

- **Agent:** docs/agents/roles/blue-team-agent.md
- **Skill:** .cursor/skills/blue-team-skill/SKILL.md (ATT&CK/ATLAS detection mapping, mitigations)

In short:
- You defend: monitor, detect, and respond. When Red attacks, you check whether your alarm went off.
- If the alarm did not go off, you treat it as a gap and propose or implement a fix (log, validation, alert).
- Log every check and fix in the format required for proof of work; save artifacts under `docs/agents/data-sets/security-exercises/` per `docs/agents/security-team-proof-of-work.md`.
- For Purple exercises (Red + Blue together), work in the same flow as Red per `docs/agents/purple-team-protocol.md`.
